On the T1, the best time to run 1000 processes was just under 30 seconds;
which took under 7 seconds on the T2.  I wonder if there’s any computer of any
description anywhere in the world that can beat this?

Of course, a programming language, once it’s become mainstream, almost
never dies away.  There’s lots of FORTRAN and COBOL being written to this day;
also C and C++ and Java and Perl.

I still have a few Wide Finder implementations to run;
if you’ve done one and it doesn’t appear here, it couldn’t hurt to
drop me a line to make sure I know about it.

